From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Proton GE Team <proton-ge@example.com>
Date: Thu, 25 Jun 2026 21:30:00 -0600
Subject: [PATCH] winedmo: Open remote HLS playlists by URL.

VRChat's in-game YouTube player uses Media Foundation Media Engine with
HTTP(S) HLS playlist URLs.  The winegstreamer path passed those URLs directly
to GStreamer's uridecodebin, which let the HLS demuxer resolve relative media
segments from the playlist URI.

The winedmo path resolved HTTP(S) sources into an anonymous IStream first and
then passed only the manifest bytes to FFmpeg through custom AVIO.  That loses
the source URL as the HLS base URI, so FFmpeg fails to detect or resolve the
playlist and falls into the media-converter placeholder path.

Detect remote HLS URLs and let FFmpeg open the original URL directly.  Keep the
existing custom bytestream/media-converter path for local files and non-HLS
streams.

Advertise the same HLS and common container MIME types through Media Engine
capability queries. Some Unity video plugins validate a URL by probing
CanPlayType() or IsTypeSupported() before passing the actual URL to Media
Foundation; returning "unsupported" there makes VRChat reject valid YouTube HLS
URLs before winedmo sees them.

Some HLS diagnostics include the full signed playlist or segment URL, which can
overflow Wine's debug output buffer when passed through wine_dbg_vlog().  Format
FFmpeg log lines into a bounded local buffer before forwarding them to Wine's
debug channel.
